						               													<description>With this adventure booklet you can experience another exciting adventure of Robin Hood and his companions. It plays around the same time as chapter 4. The story of the adventure plays independently of the others and therefore no prior knowledge of other chapters is necessary.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Since new elements and tiles from later adventures have been added, it is recommended that you have already played the basic game. All outlaws already have their own special abilities. The functions for new items can be found on the following page. No prior knowledge of this adventure is required.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Robin and his friends took the injured Guardian to the secret camp and were concerned if he would survive this unpredictable onslaught. Robin paced frantically, pondering who was behind this evil could. Because only he can save the keeper so that he can recover. It was clear that the Sheriff of Nottingham must be behind this curse, for the sheriff had been following her for a long time. The forest was a good hiding place and the guards always had great difficulty finding them. Suddenly voices were heard nearby. The sheriff's guards were alarmed, because Nottingham was swarming with soldiers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
